    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Saigon (
                        Abbott
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v07p1</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d12</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">12</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-03-17T02:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-03-17T02:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-17T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-17T02:00:00-05:00" n="12" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851<gloss target="#t_G1">G</gloss>.01/3–1749:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Saigon</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Abbott</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-17T15:00:00+08:00">March 17, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>66. In conversation with Lacy,<note n="1" xml:id="d12fn1">William S. B. Lacy,
                        Assistant Chief of the Division of Southeast Asian Affairs, on a visit to
                        Saigon.</note> myself, General Blaizot<note n="2" xml:id="d12fn2">Gen. Roger
                        Blaizot, Commander in Chief of French Forces in the Far East.</note> stated
                    second exchange of letters Bao Dai–Auriol has occurred covering many points left
                    open original agreement. Third exchange Bao Dai–Pignon being drafted will cover
                    practical application agreements including question federal services. Blaizot
                    also stated confidential parliamentary processes will be completed before
                    arrival Bao Dai April 25. Emperor will return to united independent country with
                    all preparations made for prompt transfer of authority and application of
                    agreement. Pouched Hanoi.<note n="3" xml:id="d12fn3">Repeated by the Department
                        in airgram A–267, March 18, to Paris.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Abbott</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
